         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... as much as the wise one generates consciousness [and] thinking in the virtues of the Buddha-lord, in as much your virtues have to be made recalled.    </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>362</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">After having paid homage starting with every love [and] praise, one should desire a wish as follows: Through the manner by which you, o venerable one, o ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">you have come to the end of all evils, [and] you ornated yourself beyond any measure with all the virtues. May all the beings through these good deeds of mine  </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>362</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4 #a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>670</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">precisely in this way go to the end of all evils. I will reach these virtues. I will make disappear the causes of evil. All the causes of virtues</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">may they arise vigorously for them. May the jewel of the Law which destroys all evils [and] which gives all virtues remain stable for a long time.   </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">May the whole world evolve according to the causes of the stability of the Law for a long time. For me also in all the births, for sure, from the path of the serenity and the Law,  </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">may hindrance not occur, guided by the wisdom [and] the compassion until the obtaining of the dignity of Buddha-lord inclusively.   </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">May I not give up the virtues without a being. May I become a foundation of the virtues of the omniscient starting from this one. ... In order to leave from the stūpa </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">the consciousness has to be established. And, in all births may the separation from the good ones never happen. And, may I remain carrying in my heart continuously the friendship of the good beings in all births.     </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">May I evolve according to the teaching of the good ones with body, speech [and] mind in all times. While going to see the teacher  </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">this should be done in the mind: May all the beings obtain to see in person (lit. in the eyes) the Buddha-lord beginning with Maitreya. It should be desired with consciousness in order to be agreed.   </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">May I never make anything apart from both teachers (that are) wisdom [and] compassion. Thereupon in threefold way ...   </seg></seg></choice></p>
