               <item n="m_translation_old">a1 ... as much as the wise one generates consciousness [and] thinking in the virtues of the Buddha-lord, in as much your virtues have to be made recalled.    
a2 After having paid homage starting with every love [and] praise, one should desire a wish as follows: Through the manner by which you, o venerable one, o ...
a3 you have come to the end of all evils, [and] you ornated yourself beyond any measure with all the virtues. May all the beings through these good deeds of mine  
a4 precisely in this way go to the end of all evils. I will reach these virtues. I will make disappear the causes of evil. All the causes of virtues
a5 may they arise vigorously for them. May the jewel of the Law which destroys all evils [and] which gives all virtues remain stable for a long time.   
a6 May the whole world evolve according to the causes of the stability of the Law for a long time. For me also in all the births, for sure, from the path of the serenity and the Law,  
b1 may hindrance not occur, guided by the wisdom [and] the compassion until the obtaining of the dignity of Buddha-lord inclusively.   
b2 May I not give up the virtues without a being. May I become a foundation of the virtues of the omniscient starting from this one. ... In order to leave from the stūpa 
b3 the consciousness has to be established. And, in all births may the separation from the good ones never happen. And, may I remain carrying in my heart continuously the friendship of the good beings in all births.     
b4 May I evolve according to the teaching of the good ones with body, speech [and] mind in all times. While going to see the teacher  
b5 this should be done in the mind: May all the beings obtain to see in person (lit. in the eyes) the Buddha-lord beginning with Maitreya. It should be desired with consciousness in order to be agreed.   
b6 May I never make anything apart from both teachers (that are) wisdom [and] compassion. Thereupon in threefold way ...   </item>
